I think if we end up there where poly market does become the truly liquid market across all of these kind of predictions, all of these assets, then a lot of what we are seeing with respect to insider trading, insider information becomes much more apparent. So the problem with the sports betting is that there's a one-sided bet. The casino sets the odds or you know, whomever is setting the odds and then you're either taking one side or the other. And so if you have the insider information, you're taking the side, that creates an arbitrage opportunity for you. But if you were to do that in a liquid market where there's someone taking the other side in a dynamic way, then the market very quickly moves because of the inside knowledge you have. And that inside knowledge is now reflected in the underlying asset price in the underlying odds that you get for that bet. And so poly market actually brings truth and transparency to what is currently an insider arbitrage opportunity. And it may actually solve some of these fundamental problems in in gambling."
